function count_model_rows(df_cars::DataFrame)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> g -> length(g)
end
```

This function takes a `DataFrame` named `df_cars` and groups it by the `model` column. Then, it calculates the number of rows for each model using the `length` function on the grouped data. Finally, it returns the result as an anonymous array.
